# Project #2 - Code Sharing

* Due Sep 6, 2019


### Goal

Setup your Github code repository with code from Mark.

Build a collection of pages without duplicating code.


## Step 1 - Setup Git Repo

### Register an account at [Github.com](http://Github.com)
* Free accounts for public repos
* Recommend using your human user name


### Browse my Repo
* [My Code at Github](https://github.com/Mark-Seaman/UNC-BACS350-2019-Fall)
* Browse the source code


### Fork My Repo
* Create a copy with its own history
* Remember how to get code updates from Mark

![](img/fork-repo.png)


### View Your Fork of the Repo
* Clone the repo onto each local computer
* Pin Github Desktop to Windows Start Bar

![](img/GithubDesktop.png)


### Github Desktop
* Show code that changed
* Commit changes
* Pull/Push to share changes
* Show history


### Edit Your Code Using Brackets
* Github will automatically track your changes
* Open Folder to point to "public_html/bacs350"


### Commit Changes Every Hour
* Each time you get something new working
* Do not wait too long


### Install Github Desktop on Each Computer
* Setup each computer for efficiency



## Step 2 - Debug the Render Page Pattern

